children.subject: Also interested in knowing the answer to this, as I didn't register with any team.

history.content:
Summer session enrollment is first come, first served.  Teams are not required to be formed prior to enrollment. Had that been the case, you would not have been able to enroll.

Spring semester's offering of 169 was cancelled before any students were enrolled. I don't believe in the 17 years I've been doing this that we have ever cancelled a class in CS once enrollments had begun.

children.subject:
CS169 over the summer

Do you need to have a project group before signing up, or are you able to find one after class starts? Heard that you need to sign up with a group for cs169 during the semester and wanted to see if this is still the case -- thanks!

history.content:
This might be asked somewhere already, but I have heard that I need to be enrolled with project group of 4-6 people. Is this the case for this summer as well? I had no problem being enrolled and haven't asked to fill form or anything. 

And another question, I know 169 for spring was cancelled at some point. But why? I will have to be very worried if there is a possibility of it being cancelled this summer because its cancellation will literally ruins my entire 2 years plan (I am transfer student and don't have much time or flexibility on schedule...)

Thanks in advance for help.
